body_html:
Incidentally, when you run the CPU tests (or any test?) at the moment you get errors like these:

2017-05-26 09:25:47.991881: E tensorflow/compiler/xla/service/hlo_evaluator.cc:582] TryEvaluate failed:Unimplemented: unhandled HLO ops for HloEvaluator: pad.

I think that this is something to do with having it included in one of the optimizers?

I don't think that the message should be listed as an error if it is going to appear regularly.

body:
Incidentally, when you run the CPU tests (or any test?) at the moment you get errors like these:

```
2017-05-26 09:25:47.991881: E tensorflow/compiler/xla/service/hlo_evaluator.cc:582] TryEvaluate failed:Unimplemented: unhandled HLO ops for HloEvaluator: pad.
```
I think that this is something to do with having it included in one of the optimizers?

I don't think that the message should be listed as an error if it is going to appear regularly.
